title: For Sale/Trade:  Charles Daly Superior grade 12 ga over/under by miroku w. 5 Briley extended choke tubes and browning hard case
postcontent: I have a Charles Daly Superior grade by miroku firearms. It's a 12 ga over and under, which comes with a browning hard case (Charles Daly's are similar to Brownings, this case is $200+ new).  It's got wood stock and forearm, with engraving on the action. The action works perfectly, I've never had a problem at all with the mechanics of the gun, and I've shot tens of thousands of rounds through it. I've had it for around 8 years, and shot competition for those 8 years. I sent the gun down to Briley in Texas, one of the best names in choke tubes, and had both barrels drilled and taped for choke tubes, and got extended 5 tubes for it: modified, 2 light modified (my favorite), improved cylinder, and skeet. They are lead only, as I never hunt with this shotgun. They are thin-wall choke tubes (what they put in when it didn't come drilled from the factory, so they don't have to take out a bunch of the metal in the barrel). To have this done, costed over 700 buck. I had it done by the best, and it was worth every penny. I had a kick ease installed on the gun and fitted to me by a profession gun stock carpenter, but several other people have shot it, and said it fit them great. The pad is awesome, not to sticky, not too smooth, and does a great job shock absorbing. As a competition shooter, I took very good care of it, took it apart and cleaned it almost every time I shot it, but it did have some issues when I got it. The forearm had a crack in it, which I had fixed by a professional gun stock carpenter, and he did a great job. You can tell close up, buries way better then a crack. And he fixed it GOOD, you won't have another problem with that crack. There's also some minor skuffs and scratches in the wood, and some minor sketches In the metal in unnoticeable spots, and if you look really closely in a spot or two, you can see where there used to be some super minor surface rust. Most people won't tell you all this, and so it sounds like it's all major stuff, but it's really not that noticeable.

title: For Sale:  Raw Land Acreage for bug out, gun range and isolation in Laramie, Wyoming
postcontent: Three lots of raw rural land for sale located 15 miles west of Laramie, Wyoming. Lot prices start at $48,500 for 38 acres and can be very negotiable for the right buyer (neighbor). Overhead or underground electric power is on some lots and can be brought in on lots where it is needed. Land is located on CR 44 (Big Hollow Road), 3 miles N/E of Lake Hattie, 6 miles east from National Forest and just east of Wild Horse Ranch. This land is ideal for those who want to park an RV or build a cabin and enjoy beautiful vistas with very few man made objects within miles. Personally, we are using it for a bug out when the SHTF along with being a nice retreat to target shoot and enjoy the solitude. We would be particularly interested in having like-minded neighbors that would appreciate a place to stock up and feel secure if/when the SHTF. We can build a cabin onsite using classic log building techniques .. our prototype cabin built last summer is shown in the pictures. We also have a sawmill and logs onsite, along with general construction equipment to get your property easily and economically usable for your particular needs. Please note that drilling for water is a hit and miss ordeal in this area, but you can easily haul your own water just like most everybody else living west of Laramie.  The City of Laramie also has two high volume water dispensing depots designed for rural residents. One depot is in Laramie and the other depot is at the water treatment plant which is 10 miles from the property. Bottom line is, hauling water and a cistern holding tank is far more economical and feasible for a getaway cabin. Water well, casing and pump is estimated to be around $20K and that buys a lot of water at $.25/100 gallons at the depots.I am a licensed civil engineer and have lived in Laramie 30 years. I have a local Laramie phone number and address. If interested, shoot me an email and include your phone number so we can talk about being neighbors. All pictures, with the exception of the "big valley" picture, are of the actual property available. The dirt road picture is of the private road that runs through the middle of the development. I look forward to hearing from you!

title: For Sale:  2 FNH Model 57 Chambered in 5.7x28 (NIB)
postcontent: The FN 5.7×28mm is a small-caliber, high-velocity cartridge designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium.[7] It is a bottlenecked centerfire cartridge that is somewhat similar to the .22 Hornet or .22 K-Hornet.[7] The 5.7×28mm was developed in conjunction with the FN P90 personal defense weapon (PDW) and FN Five-seven pistol, in response to NATO requests for a replacement for the 9×19mm Parabellum cartridge.[10][11] In 2002 and 2003, NATO conducted a series of tests with the intention of standardizing a PDW cartridge as a replacement for the 9×19mm Parabellum cartridge.[11] The tests compared the relative merits of the 5.7×28mm cartridge and the 4.6×30mmcartridge, which was created by Heckler & Koch as a competitor to the 5.7×28mm.[11] The NATO group subsequently recommended the 5.7×28mm cartridge, citing superior performance in testing, but the German delegation objected and the standardization process was indefinitely halted.[11] By 2006, FN's 5.7×28mm firearms—the P90 personal defense weapon and Five-seven pistol—were in service with military and police forces in over 40 nations throughout the world.[12] In the United States, 5.7×28mm firearms are currently used by numerous law enforcement agencies, including the U.S. Secret Service.[13][14] In addition to being used in the FN P90 and FN Five-seven firearms, the 5.7×28mm cartridge has subsequently been used in a number of other weapons, such as the AR-57 and FN PS90 carbines.[15][16] Excel Arms has developed four firearms chambered in 5.7×28mm, and MasterPiece Arms offers three different firearms in 5.7×28mm.[17][18] The 5.7×28mm cartridge itself is produced in a number of varieties, two of which—the SS195LF and SS197SR—are currently offered by FN to civilian shooters.I have 2 FNH 5.7x28 pistols for sale. title: For Sale:  Learn To Reload with Detroit Bullet Works
postcontent: Metallic Cartridge Reloading CourseShort Description: Teaches beginning reloader’s the basic knowledge, skills, and attitude necessary to safely reload metallic cartridges.   In the class we will cover The class is taught using an RCBS Rock Chucker Reloading kit, this kit contains 90% of what is needed to start reloading at home you will still need to purchase caliber specific item i.e. dies.(Once the class is over you will need to purchase your own equipment)    Brass selection and preparation (What is good, What is bad, Where to get quality brass from) Researching and selecting load data from multiple sources as well as some basic math formulas to predict the behavior of you newly built ammunition and how to test it and keep records We will discuss equipment selection and cover reloading die selection, case lubes, tumbling media, and much more. (You will be shown what you need to buy to load safely without breaking the bank!) Discussion of how to lay out your work area for efficiency, and some methodology about being able to load with a limited time schedule We move to the shop for some hands on loading while in the shop we will do all the prep work and load:  9mm or 45ACP (covers knowledge of taper crimped semi auto cartridges) 38 Special or 44 Magnum (Covers Knowledge of roll crimped rimmed cartridges) 223/5.56 or .308Win (Covers knowledge of bottleneck rifle cartridges)     We will cover a large amount of material in this class, but by the end you will see that reloading can be a very rewarding hobby! You will leave the class with: Loading data sheets (which we will fill out while in the shop loading) A strong base of knowledge to begin your reloading hobby with   More Details: This course is six to eight hours in length and is conducted in a classroom & shop. Each student is taught reloading safety; centerfire cartridge components; using the reloading manual and reloading data; equipment; and the metallic cartridge reloading process.Click Here To Book Your Class Today We can schedule a class at your convenience for groups of 3 or more students please email or call to make arrangements   Classes are limited to 6 students per class
